<ArticleLayout
  title="About Articulate"
  description="A brief explanation of Articulate as a reference architecture, architectural laboratory, and public journal."
  eyebrow="Project"
>
  <p>
    Articulate is an open-source, production-oriented reference architecture exploring AI-native
    systems. It is designed to make architectural reasoning visible rather than presenting only
    finished diagrams or isolated examples.
  </p>
  <p>
    The project combines working software, decisions, experiments, patterns, diagrams, models, and
    Episodes. The software provides evidence. The journal explains the significance of that evidence.
  </p>
  <p>
    The early phase is intentionally careful. Articulate has defined its purpose and principles, but
    detailed runtime architecture will emerge through documented decisions and implementation work.
  </p>
</ArticleLayout>
